## Lookup arguments

Specify exactly one of:

| argument | behavior |
|---|---|
| `id` | Direct lookup by integer ID. |
| `name` | Exact-match lookup by name (fuzzy server search, then exact `name ==` filter). Errors if zero or more than one worker matches. |

## Returned values

The data source exposes every read field of a worker. The authentication
`token` is **never** returned by reads — it is shown only once at creation (see
the [`mistershell_worker` resource](../resources/worker.md) page).

| attribute | description |
|---|---|
| `id` | Worker integer ID. |
| `name` | Worker name. |
| `description` | Worker description. |
| `location_id` | Integer ID of the location the worker is bound to. |
| `status` | Operational state: `pending`, `online`, `offline`, or `error`. See the resource page. |
| `is_default` | `true` for the system-managed bootstrap default worker. |
| `is_enabled` | Whether the worker is enabled (admin intent). |
| `active_task_count` | Number of currently active tasks. |
| `total_task_count` | Total tasks ever assigned. |
| `last_heartbeat_at` | Timestamp of the last heartbeat. |
| `connected_at` | Timestamp the worker last connected. |
| `presence_ip` | IP the worker is connected from (or the manual override). |
| `presence_ip_source` | `detected` or `manual`. |
| `config` | Opaque task-handler config JSON (free-form). See the resource page. |
| `config_version` | SHA-256-derived version hash of the applied `config`. |
| `config_schema` | JSON Schema used to validate `config`, as JSON. |
| `created_at` | Creation timestamp. |
| `updated_at` | Last-update timestamp. |

For the `status` value meanings, the default-worker constraints, and the full
`config` / `config_schema` semantics, see the
[`mistershell_worker` resource](../resources/worker.md) page.
